00:12:25,615 --> 00:12:29,361
There's a nice little quote from the director, Christopher Nolan, which is, he just talks

194
00:12:29,401 --> 00:12:35,209
about how persistence is 90% of the battle.

195
00:12:35,450 --> 00:12:37,413
And then he goes on to say, well, it's actually 70%, but 90% sounds much better.

196
00:12:43,938 --> 00:12:58,247
Something I had hoped to do with this talk and with other times that I've spoken either online or in person is just that we, everyone wants to cultivate a culture of success and an aura of success around them.

197
00:12:58,267 --> 00:13:00,488
It's the whole Facebook syndrome, right?

198
00:13:01,829 --> 00:13:03,870
No one wants to appear like they're having trouble.

199
00:13:04,290 --> 00:13:09,173
And I think that's a natural impulse, but at the same time, that can be unhealthy for the community as a whole.

200
00:13:10,254 --> 00:13:11,454
And I know for me personally.

201
00:13:13,195 --> 00:13:18,059
It wasn't until I started reading about how other developers,

202
00:13:18,139 --> 00:13:20,020
both in the games industry, but also in film,

203
00:13:20,140 --> 00:13:23,722
like, you know, other people who have started these big projects,

204
00:13:24,403 --> 00:13:30,186
had profound issues, either failures or, you know, struggles and things,

205
00:13:30,747 --> 00:13:33,889
and was able to start relating those to my own experience

206
00:13:33,949 --> 00:13:38,191
that I then was able to sort of pick up and move on.

