00:38:48,375 --> 00:38:50,696
It's not that you can look at any given game and say,

716
00:38:50,796 --> 00:38:51,877
oh, this game did it that way.

717
00:38:51,917 --> 00:38:52,858
I'm going to do it that way.

718
00:38:53,378 --> 00:38:56,920
Every game has its own problems and triumphs.

719
00:38:57,761 --> 00:39:01,343
So it is worthwhile to see if there

720
00:39:01,543 --> 00:39:03,764
are others who have tried exactly what you're going

721
00:39:03,784 --> 00:39:05,245
to try and have failed to do so.

722
00:39:05,325 --> 00:39:07,706
It's very hard to find failures, but they are out there.

723
00:39:09,007 --> 00:39:12,691
And I think you also need to ask yourself whether the costs,

724
00:39:13,612 --> 00:39:16,634
emotionally and financially, are worth the risk.

725
00:39:17,155 --> 00:39:20,918
Because we knew that we were going into this with maybe getting nothing out of it,

726
00:39:20,958 --> 00:39:22,019
and we were okay with that.

727
00:39:22,660 --> 00:39:27,745
But part of that might have been because we weren't completely bitter and burnt out at that point yet.

728
00:39:29,526 --> 00:39:30,527
So it's different for every game.

