00:39:35,287 --> 00:39:42,092
I think a lot of that has to do with, like, what is your intention as an indie developer?

731
00:39:42,273 --> 00:39:46,016
Like, is this a one and done, or are you a lifer?

732
00:39:46,616 --> 00:39:53,682
Because in my case, we, so my brother and I co-founded the studio together, and it's

733
00:39:56,336 --> 00:39:59,301
We're in the kind of indie games or die kind of mentality

734
00:39:59,401 --> 00:40:01,985
where our creations are so precious to us

735
00:40:02,245 --> 00:40:04,990
that we're going to stick with it regardless.

736
00:40:05,250 --> 00:40:08,195
And as much as he occasionally accuses me

737
00:40:08,255 --> 00:40:09,617
of George Lucas-ing the game,

738
00:40:11,882 --> 00:40:15,064
I think, uh, you know, because games have really long tails.

739
00:40:15,704 --> 00:40:19,166
And I, hopefully, like I still play the original XCOM,

740
00:40:20,007 --> 00:40:24,109
uh, and people like that, that game still has a living community.

741
00:40:24,369 --> 00:40:26,770
And not, I mean, should be so lucky, but at the same time,

742
00:40:26,810 --> 00:40:29,012
it's like, if someone plays Brigador in 10 years,

